      "startDate": "2025-01-01",
      "summary": "I'm on a small platform team with a wide scope: CI, client architecture (React/Redux), the design system, monorepo health (150+ packages), and the Electron app.\n\nI\u2019ve been the driver for engineer quality-of-life. I\u2019ve done major version upgrades to React, Node, Storybook, Turborepo, and pnpm. I've resolved tragedy-of-the-commons issues like dependency governance and flaky tests through tooling, collaboration, and just getting things done. I make sure our codebase works on all major coding agent sandboxes like Claude, Codex, and Cursor, and that the agentic coding experience is great. I\u2019ve built tools that everyone uses and extends to get their work done, including some that are now open source."
